cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
1. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on modeling the spread of epidemics through a population using network models of contacts between individuals. This falls under the scope of social and information networks.
2. cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper uses software to simulate epidemics on different network models, which could fall under the scope of software engineering.
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper uses a stochastic SIR model to simulate epidemics, which could fall under the scope of systems and control.
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses computational methods to analyze and evaluate different network models for epidemic simulations.
5. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with network models of contacts between individuals, which could fall under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
